    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Masquerades of the Chewa and neighboring peoples in Malawi, Zambia, and Angola in Africa;  they are performed at funerary ceremonies, masqueraders representing spirits of the dead.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mascarada del pueblo Chewa y las poblaciones vecinas en Malawi, Zambia y Angola en África; se llevan a cabo en las ceremonias funerarias, con enmascarados que representan los espírituos de la muerte.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Maskerades van het Chewavolk en naburige volkeren in de Afrikaanse landen Malawi, Zambia en Angola, die worden opgevoerd bij begrafenissen. De gemaskerden stellen de geesten van de doden voor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>非洲的切瓦（Chewa）部族和鄰近馬拉威、尚比亞與安哥拉內部族的化妝舞會；在喪葬典禮上表演，戴面具的舞者代表死者的靈魂。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
